<subSubSection id="D694C5B9AB5FFFB800DCFDAFFA9BFBBE" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="9E319632AB5FFFB800DCFDAFFF2DFCF2" blockId="1.[151,1437,578,1108]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB800DCFDAFFEFBFDD2" bold="true" box="[151,267,578,604]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Remarks.</emphasis>
The genus can be divided into two species group by the elytral bands. The “wide banded” species group recently includes four valid species, 
<taxonomicName id="598EEDB1AB5FFFB8026FFD8BFCB6FD0F" authority="(Pascoe, 1858)" baseAuthorityName="Pascoe" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[548,838,614,641]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sthenias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsalis">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB8026FFD8BFD6BFD0E" box="[548,667,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">A. dorsalis</emphasis>
(Pascoe, 1858)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="598EEDB1AB5FFFB8031BFD8BFB43FD0F" authority="(Breuning, 1956)" baseAuthorityName="Breuning" baseAuthorityYear="1956" box="[848,1203,614,641]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anaches" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="medioalbus">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB8031BFD8BFC1EFD0E" box="[848,1006,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">A. medioalbus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FA1FEBC3AB5FFFB803B1FD8BFB5CFD0F" author="Breuning, S." box="[1018,1196,614,641]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="229 - 236" refId="ref4882" refString="Breuning, S. (1956) Die Ostasien-Cerambyciden im Museum A. Koenig, Bonn. Bonner Zoologische Beitrage, 7 (1 - 3), 229 - 236." type="journal article" year="1956">Breuning, 1956</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="598EEDB1AB5FFFB804F6FD8BFF2BFD2A" authority="(Lazarev, 2020)" baseAuthorityName="Lazarev" baseAuthorityYear="2020" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sthenias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="murzini">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB804F6FD8BFADFFD0E" box="[1213,1327,614,640]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">A. murzini</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="FA1FEBC3AB5FFFB80570FD8BFF23FD2A" author="Lazarev, M. A." pageId="1" pageNumber="124" refId="ref5336" refString="Lazarev, M. A. (2020) A new species of genus Sthenias Laporte, 1840 (Coleoptera: Cerambycidae) from Sichuan province of China. Entomologische Blatter und Coleoptera, 116, 057 - 059." type="book" year="2020">Lazarev, 2020</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="598EEDB1AB5FFFB80153FD67FD42FD2A" authority="Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013" authorityName="Holzschuh &amp; Lin" authorityYear="2013" box="[280,690,650,676]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anaches" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="wenhsini">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB80153FD67FE6CFD2A" box="[280,412,650,676]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">A. wenhsini</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA1FEBC3AB5FFFB801E8FD67FD42FD2A" author="Holzschuh, C. &amp; Lin, Y. - L." box="[419,690,650,676]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="147 - 158" refId="ref5212" refString="Holzschuh, C. &amp; Lin, Y. - L. (2013) Beitrag zur Bockkaferfauna von Taiwan, mit Beschreibung neuer Arten (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). In: Lin, M. - Y. &amp; Chen, C. - C. (Eds.), In memory of Mr. Wenhsin Lin. Formosa Ecological Company, Taipei, pp. 147 - 158." type="book chapter" year="2013">Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. They share the common characters: 1) the whitish pubescent part on elytra nearly or even more than half of elytra length in lateral view; 2) the greyish parts within the pubescent band form two bands, separated by a white pubescent polyline. In this paper, we do not try to solve this “ 
<taxonomicName id="598EEDB1AB5FFFB8057DFD3FFA60FD62" baseAuthorityName="Pascoe" baseAuthorityYear="1858" box="[1334,1424,722,748]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sthenias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dorsalis">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB8057DFD3FFA60FD62" box="[1334,1424,722,748]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">dorsalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
” species group except the new synonyms. 
<taxonomicName id="598EEDB1AB5FFFB8022CFD1BFBF0FC9E" authority="(Gressitt, 1939)" baseAuthorityName="Gressitt" baseAuthorityYear="1939" box="[615,1024,758,784]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anaches" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cylindricus">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB8022CFD1BFCB9FC9E" box="[615,841,758,784]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Anaches cylindricus</emphasis>
(Gressitt, 1939)
</taxonomicName>
neither belong to this species group, nor belong to the following species group which includes the new species. This species resembles to species of the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="598EEDB1AB5FFFB8017AFCD3FD88FCD6" authority="Breuning, 1961" authorityName="Breuning" authorityYear="1961" box="[305,632,830,856]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Albosthenias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB8017AFCD3FE32FCD6" box="[305,450,830,856]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Albosthenias</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA1FEBC3AB5FFFB80182FCD3FD88FCD6" author="Breuning, S." box="[457,632,830,856]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="183 - 284" refId="ref4914" refString="Breuning, S. (1961) Catalogue des Lamiaires du Monde (Col. Ceramb.). Verlag des Museums G. Frey, Tutzing bei Munchen, (4), 183 - 284." type="journal article" year="1961">Breuning, 1961</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="598EEDB1AB5FFFB8035BFCD3FBE0FCD7" authority="Dejean, 1835" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1835" box="[784,1040,830,857]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Sthenias" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB8035BFCD3FC9FFCD6" box="[784,879,830,856]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">Sthenias</emphasis>
Dejean, 1835
</taxonomicName>
. It won’t be discussed in this paper either.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="9E319632AB5FFFB8008CFC6BFA9BFBBE" blockId="1.[151,1437,578,1108]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">
The new species belongs to the “narrow banded” species group, which includes three species, 
<taxonomicName id="598EEDB1AB5FFFB80547FC6BFEB9FC4A" authority="(Gressitt, 1942)" baseAuthorityName="Gressitt" baseAuthorityYear="1942" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anaches" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="albaninus">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB80547FC6BFA6CFC2E" box="[1292,1436,902,928]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">A. albaninus</emphasis>
(Gressitt, 1942)
</taxonomicName>
, 
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB8011EFC47FE1FFC4A" box="[341,495,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">A. m-signatus</emphasis>
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB801BEFC47FDBFFC4A" bold="true" box="[501,591,938,964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">sp. nov.</emphasis>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="598EEDB1AB5FFFB802C7FC47FBF5FC4A" authority="Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013" authorityName="Holzschuh &amp; Lin" authorityYear="2013" box="[652,1029,938,964]" class="Insecta" family="Cerambycidae" genus="Anaches" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="yitingi">
<emphasis id="ACFA4A20AB5FFFB802C7FC47FD03FC4A" box="[652,755,938,964]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="124">A. yitingi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="FA1FEBC3AB5FFFB802B2FC47FBF5FC4A" author="Holzschuh, C. &amp; Lin, Y. - L." box="[761,1029,938,964]" pageId="1" pageNumber="124" pagination="147 - 158" refId="ref5212" refString="Holzschuh, C. &amp; Lin, Y. - L. (2013) Beitrag zur Bockkaferfauna von Taiwan, mit Beschreibung neuer Arten (Coleoptera, Cerambycidae). In: Lin, M. - Y. &amp; Chen, C. - C. (Eds.), In memory of Mr. Wenhsin Lin. Formosa Ecological Company, Taipei, pp. 147 - 158." type="book chapter" year="2013">Holzschuh &amp; Lin, 2013</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
. They share the common characters: 1) the whitish pubescent part on elytra much less than half of elytra length in lateral view, only nearly one third or even less than one third; 2) the greyish parts within the pubescent band form only one transverse band. In this paper, we describe one new species, and make additional descriptions of the male genitalia of the other three species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
